==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sanctimony
<hw>Sanc"ti*mo*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sanctimonia</ets>, fr. <ets>sanctus</ets> holy: cf. OF.
<ets>sanctimonie</ets>. See <er>Saint</er>.]</ety> <def>Holiness;
devoutness; scrupulous austerity; sanctity; especially, outward or
artificial saintliness; assumed or pretended holiness; hypocritical
devoutness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her pretense is a pilgrimage; . . . which holy undertaking with
most austere <qex>sanctimony</qex> she accomplished.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sanction</ent>⟦br⟧
